        "mainbody": "'''Lonthalin Mintar''' was a [[human]] [[wizard]] in [[Baldur's Gate]] in the mid–14{{th}} century [[DR]].",
        "Activities": "Lonthalin, like many of his fellow minor mages, worked from a stall in [[the Wide]], an open market of Baldur's Gate, and was a fixture there around [[1366 DR]]. He specialized in [[spell]]s that provided temporary cosmetic adornments, such as fantastic hairstyles, tattoos, scents, and changes in color and making revealing costumes cling. He could make disguises for a fee of 25–100 [[gp]]."
